## üèõÔ∏è **Project Overview**
Siam Blessing is a cultural heritage platform showcasing Thai traditions, festivals, and blessings. This project combines modern web technologies with traditional Thai aesthetics to create an immersive cultural experience.

---

## üé® **Design & UI Framework References**

### **CSS Framework & Grid System**
- **CSS Grid Layout**
  - Source: [CSS-Tricks Complete Guide to Grid](https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/complete-guide-grid/)
  - Author: Chris House
  - Usage: Traditional Thai temple-inspired grid layouts
  ```css
  .temple-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    grid-gap: 2rem;
    grid-template-areas: 
      "header header header"
      "sidebar main main"
      "footer footer footer";
  }
  ```

- **Flexbox Patterns**
  - Reference: [A Complete Guide to Flexbox](https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/)
  - Author: Chris Coyier
  - Usage: Navigation, blessing card layouts, cultural element alignment

### **Typography & Fonts**
- **Google Fonts - Sarabun**
  - Source: [Google Fonts - Sarabun](https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Sarabun)
  - Designer: Cadson Demak
  - License: SIL Open Font License 1.1
  - Usage: Primary Thai-friendly font for body text
  ```html
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Sarabun:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  ```

- **Google Fonts - Prompt**
  - Source: [Google Fonts - Prompt](https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Prompt)
  - Designer: Cadson Demak
  - License: SIL Open Font License 1.1
  - Usage: Headings and Thai text display
  ```html
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Prompt:wght@300;400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  ```

