## üîç **SEO & Cultural Content Optimization**

### **Structured Data for Cultural Content**
- **Schema.org Cultural Markup**
  - Reference: [Schema.org](https://schema.org/)
  - Usage: Thai cultural events, places, traditions
```json
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "CulturalEvent",
  "name": "Songkran Festival",
  "description": "Traditional Thai New Year celebration",
  "location": {
    "@type": "Country",
    "name": "Thailand"
  },
  "startDate": "2024-04-13",
  "endDate": "2024-04-15"
}
```

### **Multilingual SEO**
- **Hreflang Implementation**
  - Reference: [Google Hreflang Guide](https://developers.google.com/search/docs/advanced/crawling/localized-versions)
  - Usage: Thai and English content targeting
```html
<link rel="alternate" hreflang="th" href="https://pigletpeakkung.github.io/Siam-Blessing/th/">
<link rel="alternate" hreflang="en" href="https://pigletpeakkung.github.io/Siam-Blessing/en/">
<link rel="alternate" hreflang="x-default" href="https://pigletpeakkung.github.io/Siam-Blessing/">
```

### **Open Graph for Cultural Sharing**
- **Cultural Content Meta Tags**
```html
<meta property="og:title" content="Siam Blessing - Thai Cultural Heritage">
<meta property="og:description" content="Discover the beauty of Thai traditions, festivals, and blessings">
<meta property="og:image" content="/assets/images/thai-temple-og.jpg">
<meta property="og:locale" content="th_TH">
<meta property="og:locale:alternate" content="en_US">
```

