## üé® **CSS Techniques & Thai Design Patterns**

### **Traditional Thai Design Elements**
- **CSS Shapes & Patterns**
  - Reference: [CSS Shapes](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Shapes)
  - Usage: Lotus petals, temple architecture, traditional patterns
```css
.lotus-petal {
  width: 100px;
  height: 100px;
  background: linear-gradient(45deg, #FFB6C1, #FF69B4);
  border-radius: 50% 10% 50% 10%;
  transform-origin: center bottom;
}

.thai-pattern {
  background-image: 
    radial-gradient(circle at 25% 25%, #FFD700 2px, transparent 2px),
    radial-gradient(circle at 75% 75%, #FF9933 2px, transparent 2px);
  background-size: 20px 20px;
}
```

### **CSS Custom Properties for Thai Themes**
- **Cultural Color Variables**
```css
:root {
  /* Traditional Thai Colors */
  --thai-gold: #FFD700;
  --royal-blue: #003366;
  --temple-red: #CC0000;
  --saffron: #FF9933;
  --lotus-pink: #FFB6C1;
  --bamboo-green: #228B22;
  
  /* Thai Typography */
  --thai-font-family: 'Sarabun', 'Prompt', sans-serif;
  --thai-line-height: 1.8;
  --thai-letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  
  /* Cultural Spacing */
  --temple-spacing: 2.5rem;
  --blessing-padding: 1.618rem; /* Golden ratio */
}
```

